MELBOURNE, April 12 (Reuters Breakingviews) - Saul Griffith, author of “The Big Switch”, tells The Exchange why neither hydrogen nor carbon capture can tackle global warming. Instead, electrifying everything from cars to stoves will, thanks to ample sun and wind Down Under. It’d spark a jobs and exports boom, too. Listen to the podcast  Follow @AntonyMCurrie on Twitter (The host is a Reuters Breakingviews columnist. The opinions expressed are his own. Refiles to fix link.) Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.